        'terms__title' => 'Terms of Use',

        'terms__scope_title' => '1. Scope of Application',
        'terms__scope_text' => 'By using our services, you confirm that you have read and accepted these Terms of Use. They may be updated (due to changes in law, BSP/SEC rules or internal CapitureX policies). We recommend checking regularly to stay up to date.',

        'terms__aml_title' => '2. Anti-Money Laundering and Counter-Terrorist Financing',
        'terms__aml_text' => 'As a registered Virtual Asset Service Provider, CapitureX fully complies with the Anti-Money Laundering Act (Republic Act No. 9160), BSP Circulars, and SEC regulations. Customers must be aware of the applicable rules. This information is publicly available on the BSP and SEC websites. CapitureX takes all measures to prevent fraud, money laundering and terrorist financing. To use the services, customers must be at least 18 years old. Any fraudulent, illegal, improper, immoral or unethical use is strictly prohibited. CapitureX reserves the right to block access without notice.',

        'terms__kyc_title' => '2.1 KYC Identification (Know Your Customer)',
        'terms__kyc_text' => 'CapitureX identifies all individuals or entities reaching the legal transaction threshold as per Philippine regulations. Identification is conducted exclusively online at capiturex.net. It is based on official ID, proof of address, selfie and AML form. After Compliance validation, customers may transact above the legal limit. CapitureX reserves the right to adjust transaction volumes based on provided information.<br /> Customers agree that their data will be stored for the legally required period (usually 5–10 years), primarily for AML record-keeping. Customers also authorise inspection by BSP, SEC or CapitureX AML auditors. No sharing for marketing or commercial purposes.',

        'terms__general_title' => '3. General Provisions',

        'terms__services_title' => '3.1 Our Services',
        'terms__services_text' => 'CapitureX facilitates the exchange of cryptocurrencies for fiat and vice-versa. We offer four main services:<br /> Crypto ATMs, Point-of-Sale Partners, OTC, and the online exchange platform capiturex.net.<br /> Important: CapitureX does NOT custody customer funds or assets of any kind.',

        'terms__offer_title' => '3.2 Offer and Availability',
        'terms__offer_text' => 'Through our services, CapitureX offers:<br /> - Purchase of Bitcoin, Ethereum, Litecoin, Monero, USDT (Ethereum), USDT (Polygon), Dogecoin, Cardano, Polkadot against PHP (Philippine Peso) and USD (US Dollar).<br /> - Sale of the same assets against PHP and USD.<br /> Note: at Crypto ATMs the offer is limited:<br /> - Purchase of Bitcoin, Ethereum, Litecoin, Monero against PHP and USD.<br /> - Sale of Bitcoin and Litecoin against PHP.<br /> We strive to keep cryptocurrencies available. In case of unavailability, we reserve the right to refuse buy/sell orders, notifying the customer as soon as possible.',

        'terms__prices_title' => '3.3 Prices / Rates',
        'terms__prices_text' => 'Prices displayed to the customer are valid at the time of purchase or sale. They are based on rates from trading platforms.*',

        'terms__payment_title' => '3.4 Payment Methods',
        'terms__payment_text' => 'We accept the following payment methods:<br /> <b>POS Services:</b><br /> - PHP – coins and notes.<br /> <b>Crypto ATMs:</b><br /> - Philippine Peso notes: common denominations.<br /> <b>OTC and Online Platform capiturex.net:</b><br /> - Bank transfer / GCash / Maya / remittance (see section 6.1)',

        'terms__fees_title' => '3.5 Exchange Fees',
        'terms__fees_text' => 'Every transaction with CapitureX includes fees. These are already included in the displayed crypto price. Customers can refer to a trading platform* to estimate fee levels.<br /> Additional fixed fees may apply and will be shown before the transaction starts.',

        'terms__verification_title' => '3.6 Transaction Verification',
        'terms__verification_text' => 'Every transaction can be verified publicly on the blockchain.<br /> ADA → https://explorer.cardano.org<br /> BTC → https://mempool.space<br /> DOGE → https://dogechain.info<br /> DOT → https://polkadot.subscan.io<br /> ETH → https://etherscan.io<br /> LTC → https://litecoinblockexplorer.net<br /> XMR → https://www.exploremonero.com<br /> USDT (Ethereum) → https://etherscan.io<br /> USDT (Polygon) → https://polygonscan.com',

        'terms__timeframe_title' => '3.7 Transaction Timeframe',
        'terms__timeframe_text' => 'After initiation, funds are sent immediately to the customer’s wallet (OTC/Broker) or Paper-Wallet linked wallet (ATMs/POS). For validation, the transaction requires at least one blockchain confirmation. Most take seconds. In rare cases, due to network fees, delays of minutes to hours may occur. CapitureX is not liable for such delays.',

        'terms__paper_wallet_title' => '3.8 The Paper-Wallet',
        'terms__paper_wallet_text' => 'CapitureX provides each customer with a Paper-Wallet for ATM/POS transactions. This is the physical representation of a digital wallet on the blockchain. It consists of two key elements:<br /> - Private key: secret string that allows access to the wallet funds. It is the password for signing transactions and spending. The private key must be kept secure and confidential – anyone with access controls the funds.<br /> - Public key: generated from the private key, used to receive funds and check transaction status. Can be shared publicly.<br /> CapitureX keeps no copy of the Paper-Wallet and accepts no liability for loss, theft, damage or destruction (intentional or negligent). By accepting the services, the customer assumes full responsibility for the private key. <u>Claims after 14 days are excluded.</u>',

        'terms__sale_case_title' => '3.9 Special Rules for Selling',
        'terms__sale_case_text' => 'When selling, the customer declares sole ownership and responsibility for the sending wallet and confirms no illegal activity is linked. CapitureX checks if the address appears on official lists of illicit addresses. The customer must send the exact requested amount. Network fees are the customer’s responsibility. We strongly recommend native wallets (e.g. Bluewallet, Trust Wallet, MetaMask) as only they show accurate network fees. Sending from exchange wallets is strongly discouraged. Wrong amount or delay >30 minutes renders the transaction invalid. The customer bears full responsibility and refund costs.<br /><br /> <i>(*) Trading platforms: Based on supply/demand, enable buying/selling/exchanging crypto for fiat. Known examples: Binance, PDAX, Coins.ph, Maya, GCash partners...</i>',

        'terms__atm_title' => '4. Crypto ATM Service',

        'terms__atm_id_title' => '4.1 Identification',
        'terms__atm_id_text' => 'Every ATM transaction requires identification via phone number and M-TAN code receipt. This ensures anonymous customers do not exceed the legal transaction limit, above which KYC is mandatory. CapitureX records and stores phone numbers. We are not liable if customers use multiple numbers to circumvent the law.',

        'terms__atm_commit_title' => '4.2 When the customer commits to the transaction?',
        'terms__atm_commit_text' => 'On purchase: commitment occurs when cash is inserted into the ATM. No withdrawal accepted. On sale: commitment occurs when crypto is sent to the provided address. No withdrawal accepted.',

        'terms__atm_complaints_title' => '4.3 Complaints',
        'terms__atm_complaints_text' => 'For technical issues (e.g. no Paper-Wallet printed, no cash dispensed), contact support immediately (see section 8). CapitureX resolves after review. If no cash is dispensed, refund via cashback on the same ATM network. <u>Claims after 14 days are excluded.</u> We are not liable for insertion of wrong currency.',

        'terms__pos_title' => '5. POS Service',

        'terms__pos_id_title' => '5.1 Identification',
        'terms__pos_id_text' => 'Every POS counter transaction is conducted by the partner’s attendant. They visually verify anonymous customers do not exceed the legal limit. Registered customers are verified against KYC documents. CapitureX is not liable for attempts to circumvent the law.',

        'terms__pos_commit_title' => '5.2 When the customer commits to the transaction?',
        'terms__pos_commit_text' => 'On purchase: commitment occurs when cash is handed to the attendant. No withdrawal accepted.<br /> On sale: commitment occurs when crypto is sent. No withdrawal accepted.',

        'terms__otc_broker_title' => '6. OTC and Online Broker Service',

        'terms__transfers_title' => '6.1 Bank Transfers / GCash / Maya',
        'terms__transfers_text' => 'CapitureX accepts GCash, Maya, bank transfers and remittance from Philippine accounts. For international remittances, the customer must verify feasibility beforehand. We may request additional information on fund origin. Persistent doubts after 30 days may lead to relationship termination and refund. Interbank or e-wallet fees are the customer’s responsibility. We are not liable for delays.',

        'terms__broker_init_title' => '6.2 Order Execution on Online Broker',
        'terms__broker_init_text' => 'CapitureX executes buy/sell at market price upon fund receipt. Crypto is highly volatile. We are not liable for price differences between order placement and receipt. The customer accepts this by proceeding with the transaction.',

        'terms__otc_trading_title' => '6.3 OTC Specifics',
        'terms__otc_trading_text' => 'On purchase: negotiation starts upon fund receipt. If no fulfilment within 30 days, order is cancelled and funds refunded. We are not liable for fees or delays.<br /> On sale: negotiation starts upon receipt in destination wallet. If no fulfilment within 30 days, cancellation and blockchain return. Network fees are customer’s responsibility.',

        'terms__personal_wallet_title' => '6.4 Personal Wallet Specifics',
        'terms__personal_wallet_text' => 'For OTC or online platform transactions, the customer must provide their own wallet and confirm ownership. For large amounts, we conduct one-time verification via Satoshi test. Address change triggers re-test. Costs are customer’s responsibility. The wallet must not be linked to illegal activity. In case of doubt, we may terminate the relationship.',

